article.headline: Stony Brook 69, Army 44
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- D.J. Munir scored 26 points to lead Stony Brook over Army 69-44 Thursday night. Leading 31-15 at halftime, the Seawolves (2-3) pulled away from Army in the second half, twice taking 28-point leads in the final four minutes. Cori Spencer scored 13 points for Stony Brook, while Mike Orfini had 12 points. Mike Popoka had nine points and five steals, and Mitchell Beauford added three steals. Adeniyi Amadou led Army (3-5) with nine points. The Black Knights shot just 28 percent from the floor.
